<br>
Bzzz, bzzz, bzzz. Pssst, pssst, psst.<br>
<br>
Did you hear? Did you hear?<br>
<br>
As a woman, I will admit to being one to dish/gossip.<br>
<br>
The problem is, I want truth and fact - not conjecture or assumptions based on what you think you know. <br>
<br>
In the EQ community, there is an awful plague of rumors that spreads quickly, leaving many untruths in it's wake. Most of the time we may not realize we are perpetuating the rumor when we relay it to the next person 'in confidence'. <br>
<br>
Here's the thing. <br>
<br>
Most people in the EQ community seem to be a bit more conservative than I am. I don't mind displaying my life for all to see. I'm not worried about what might happen due to my openess. <br>
<br>
However, some people *are* more conservative, and that should be respected. On that same note, if YOU are quick to pass rumors because you are hateful and full of spite, be prepared to reap what you sow.<br>
<br>
Also, if you are close friends with someone, then all of sudden that friendship falls away - I think relaying private information to strangers and whoever else might listen is just fucked up. <br>
Get a grip, get some class, and shut your fucking mouth.<br>
<br>
This also goes for posting/displaying/relaying information that is posted in private mediums. Why on earth would you do that?<br>
<br>
Finally, be sure to get the facts before opening your mouth. I mean, if you are going to gossip, at least get the facts straight.  In the end, you will be seen as the complete idiot that you are. Spiteful, ignorant and tasteless. Class act you are not.<br>
<br>
Now I feel better. <p><table><tr><td><a href=http://pub16.ezboard.com/bdaeja><img 

