<br>
How many times have you heard about the two people that were so in love with each other in game only to find out that the girl was really a a guy?  What was the reprocussion of his actions?  Nothing...  he goes on living his normal life without any damage done to him.  Guilty conscious may be the only reprocusion but because people aren't &quot;real&quot; in EQ.. the guilt is soon departed with sort of a &quot;I got away with it&quot; attitude.<br>
<br>
I've been in the middle of, and more often witnessed many messy, messy relationship &quot;break ups&quot; due to miscommunication.  It always amazes me how quickly people will discard a once treasured friend because they heard something and never bothered to give their friend the benefit of the doubt by just listening to their side of the situation.<br>
<br>
Unfortunately though, there are people out there that don't want to listen.  It came as quite a shock to me one day when I finally realized that there are people that <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>want</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->  drama in their lives.  They need this &quot;epic&quot; feeling to make them feel important I guess.. sometimes I think it's the only way they feel alive.  Sometimes people have had so much drama in their lives that they don't know how to be a person or how to function unless there is drama in their lives.<br>
<br>
I know this though:  I have friends that I adore.  Nothing will ever get in the way of my relationships with them.  No matter how many times they fall on their face, as a friend I have to remember that it is <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>their right to fuck up</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.  It's not my right to gossip or to question.  As a friend it's my job (if you will) to confide, to help, and to suggest.  Not to judge or make matters worse.  To love and forgive; that is being a friend. <p><img src="http://www.ipleysuck.com/pics/bb.jpg">

